'''Richard Stallman on Free Software in Education'''

URL = http://educationbridges.net/k12opensource/wp-content/uploads/rms.mp3

Summary at http://stevehargadon.blogspot.com/2006/10/richard-stallman-on-free-software-in.html


=Description=


"In the interview, Richard defines the use of the word "free" in the context of software. He also defines the four essential freedoms that are behind the Free Software Movement, and the four reasons that he believes that schools should use exclusively Free Software (see also his essay on this topic). And lots more--including the fact that he likes Wikipedia."


